{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 2067700, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Varce", "body": "For some reason there is a faction of people that believe killing the NPCs in the stands isn't a mandatory part of this fight. I haven't found it anywhere else so I confirmed it myself, [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=159386]Iron Bomb[/url] DOES STACK! This will absolutely wipe your raid if you try to ignore it.", "date": "2014-12-13T01:06:19-06:00", "rating": 14, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "During the live raid at Blizzcon, one (possibly both) of the guilds opted to skip the stands mechanic. I've had folks tell me the stands are not necessary because of this. As if any of us are Midwinter/Method quality. Do the stands!", "creationdate": "2015-01-07T12:37:23-06:00", "id": 824691, "rating": 3, "commentid": 2067700, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Vaufe", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It depends on difficulty and gear level. If you're overgeared and/or have really good DPS, you can kill him before it becomes a problem. I definitely wouldn't recommend it when leaning the fight, though. Ignoring them is a much harder tactic, although it's a little bit faster.", "creationdate": "2015-01-22T09:48:45-06:00", "id": 831220, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2067700, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "defektunge", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 2068321, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Raventus", "body": "Killing him is fairly easy.\r\n\r\n[b]Chain Hurl:[/b]\r\n\r\nAssign which healer and 3 dps go into the chain hurl. Recommending melee, since they could get some dps on while he's charging up Chain Hurl and ranged dont have to move into the boss. \r\n\r\n[b]Berserker Rush:[/b]\r\n\r\nAs ranged kiting the boss into the fire, make sure you're located near the flame that spawned [b]second[/b]. This is to make sure the fire doesn't despawn on you as soon as the boss is supposed to get hit.\r\n\r\nYou can walk over the ledge behind the tiger pits. \r\n\r\n[b]Impale:[/b]\r\n\r\nEven if it doesn't look like it on the first cast, Impale does alot of damage on the second cast.\r\nTanks should activate a defensive cooldown as tank on the second impale.\r\n\r\n[b]Crowd:[/b]\r\n\r\nIn the crowd, try and focus the Iron Bombers and the ogres, as these are the only ones actually affecting the raid. The orc grunts can mostly be ignored.", "date": "2014-12-13T17:30:27-06:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
