{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 2172201, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Eilonthay", "body": "Too busy dancing around Kargath in the arena to read the dialogue?  Or maybe you're not in the mood for a faceroll to find out?  Here it is!  Enjoy!  =D\n\n[quote]Jhorn the Mad yells:  This's gotta be a mistake!  These puny squishies be the scourge of Nagrand?  They look like Elekk poodoo.\nThoktar Ironskull yells:  Dey gonna look like puddles after dis fight.\nJhorn the Mad yells:  Ha!  Today's games honor great sorcerer king!  We gonna see his bloody victory over the orcs at the Battle of Red spires!\nThoktar Ironskull yells:  I hope dese weaklings die better'n they smell.\nJhorn the Mad yells:  We'll see what dese competitors be made of, Thoktar, just as soon as what dey be made of gets splattered across the arena!  HAHAHAHA!\nThoktar Ironskull yells:  HAHAHAHAHA!\n\nJhorn the Mad yells:  Now, playing our mighty king, scream his name and bash a skull for the Shadow of Highmaul, champion of games, Vul'gor!\nJhorn the Mad yells:  Time to spill blood and die for Highmaul!  The Battle of Red Spires begins!\nVul'gor yells:  Glory and death!\nVul'gor yells:  Break you!\nJhorn the Mad yells:  These wimps be taking more limbs than losing 'em!\nThoktar Ironskull yells:  Didn't we win Battle o' Red Spires?\nJhorn the Mad yells:  Looks like they don't care they're supposed to die.\nThoktar Ironskull yells:  Disrespectin' our heritage won't get 'em invited to next year's games.\nJhorn the Mad yells:  The punies...defeated, Vul'gor!\nThoktar Ironskull yells:  How tiny mens beat mighty Vul'gor?\n\nKargath Bloadefist yells:  Enough!  I will show these weaklings what a true champion is capable of.\nJhorn the Mad yells:  The sorcerer king!  Here!  King only leaves palace to witness legendary battles.\nImperator Mar'gok yells:  You honor us, Kargath.  I will enjoy watching you fight in the arena again, even with your...handicap.\nKargath Bladefist yells:  The pleasure is mine.  The crowd deserves a superior gladiator, seeing as the last one fell so easily.\nImperator Mar'gok yells:  Gladiators!  Seize this opportunity to die gloriously, for your names will be carved into history.  Let the battle begin!\n\nKargath Bladefist yells:  You owe me a fight, cowards.\nKargath Bladefist yells:  There is no escape.\nKargath Bladefist yells:  Fool!  You'll need more than flames to finish me!\nKargath Bladefist yells:  You think you're clever?  You're next to burn!\nKargath Bladefist yells:  Time to spill your blood!\nKargath Bladefist yells:  Coward!  You can't hide behind these traps forever!\nKargath Bladefist yells:  Let's give the crowd something to chew on.\nHighmaul Sweeper says:  HAHAHAHAHA!\nImperator Mar'gok yells:  Finish him.  (said at somewhere between 8-10%)\nKargath Bladefist says:  And that's...one hundred.[/quote]\n\nFor those that don't recognize the reference to Kargath's last words, fret not, it's actually fairly easy to forget now that it's been several months and you've probably done most, if not all, of the zones and are currently raiding, potentially on several toons.  It's in reference to something that happened in the very, very beginning of WoD.  If you can recall, right after you accept Khadgar's mission, you end up leaping through the Dark Portal to an alternate Draenor, where you end up shutting down the Portal to keep the Iron Horde from going through anymore than they already have.  You're trapped and alone - but wait, maybe not!  After shutting down the portal, you sneak off behind it and head out into the jungle, in the process saving hapless draenei and gathering allies.  Right after you [url=http://www.wowhead.com/quest=34423/altar-altercation]part ways with Ariok[/url], you end up getting [url=http://www.wowhead.com/quest=34429/kill-your-hundred]trapped in an arena[/url].  And the circle is complete.  After that, it's a mad dash through several more quests, a quick boat ride where you part ways with your Horde or Alliance counterparts, and make a landing in Shadowmoon Valley or Frostfire Ridge to build a fort.  =P\n\nAfterwards, there's a cinematic where apparently Cho'gall breaks free and escapes and the Imperator has a minor freak out and locks down the complex.\n\n[quote]Imperator Mar'gok says:  Cho'gall!\nCho'gall says:  You thought to imprison us, Mar'gok?  (You could never control us!)\nImperator Mar'gok says:  Guards!  Stop him!\nCho'gall says:  Destroy them all.  Raze this city to the ground!  (The stones will be ours!  All shall fall to darkness!)\nImperator Mar'gok says:  Seal the gates!  Protect the palace!  Highmaul will never fall to the likes of you.[/quote]", "date": "2015-04-25T01:44:38-05:00", "rating": 14, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-04-25T02:09:29-05:00", 2, "Eilonthay"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 2182625, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Goldenspirit", "body": "I'm surprised not a single person mentions the fact that in WoD, you're in the past, and in TBC, you're in the present, and you can see Kargath in both timelines, even though he was obviously killed in WoD....? Seems odd just for me or what?", "date": "2015-05-13T13:14:16-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "That would be the case if it was JUST the past... but you are in an Alternate Universe, so therefore, being in an AU, events work differently than a simple to the past thing. It's a little hard to explain.", "creationdate": "2015-05-14T15:53:44-05:00", "id": 869557, "rating": 3, "commentid": 2182625, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Macamirunni", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Basically, Garrosh created a fork in the timeline when he traveled back, rather than altering the existing timeline. In the new fork, he took over the Horde on Draenor, and didn't invade Azeroth through the Dark Portal until 20 or so years later. Then instead of invading alternate-Azeroth (which had likely been eaten alive by the Scourge by then), he invaded mainline-Azeroth. And that's where we are as the new expansion starts and you go to Tanaan Jungle at 90.", "creationdate": "2015-07-22T02:23:59-05:00", "id": 886454, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2182625, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Difdi", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "WoD is in the past, but in an alternate reality. Like how Blackhand kills Orgrim in WoD but in Azeroth Orgrim killed Blackhand and became Warchief.", "creationdate": "2016-04-17T10:58:00-05:00", "id": 938593, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2182625, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "KenjiT28", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
